rob_ev_ac: The envelopes containing the random numbers were kept in a box. This box was securely locked . Only the head nurse had access to the box. The envelopes were opaque, they contained a slip containing the group to which the baby was randomized. Serial numbers were written on the front of the envelope. The randomization was done by some one not involved with the study. Hence no one could predict which group the next baby would go into. ROP examinations are done once a week, on a designated day, so the box was opened only at that time.

notes: any exam elligible but only first extrated

rob_ev_io: 13 of 55 examinations were exlucded entirely for unintentional protocol violations, equipment failure, or inability to obtain one-minute pulse oximetry. Not stated from which group, how they knew they were protocol violaters, etc… should use ITT analysis
